17\n| Rowspan=\"5\"| {{hlist|Digital download|[[music streaming|streaming]]}}\n| Bee's Knees Dance Remix\n| rowspan=\"5\"| {{hlist|We the Best|Epic}}\n| <ref name=\"bkd\">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/wild-thoughts-bees-knees-dance-remix-feat-rihanna-bryson/1259402435|title=Wild Thoughts (feat. Rihanna & Bryson Tiller) [Bee's Knees Dance Remix] \u2013 Single by DJ Khaled on Apple Music|website=iTunes|accessdate=10 December 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"bkd2\"/>\n|-\n| Dave Aud\u00e9 Dance Remix\n| <ref name=\"dad\">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/wild-thoughts-feat-rihanna-bryson-tiller-dave-aud\u00e9/1261030203|title=Wild Thoughts (feat. Rihanna & Bryson Tiller) [Dave Aud\u00e9 Dance Remix] \u2013 Single by DJ Khaled on Apple Music|website=iTunes|accessdate=10 December 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"dad2\"/>\n|-\n| Medasin Dance Remix\n| <ref name=\"Medasin Dance\">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/wild-thoughts-feat-rihanna-bryson-tiller-medasin-dance/1259402482|title=Wild Thoughts (feat. Rihanna & Bryson Tiller) [Medasin Dance Remix] \u2013 Single by DJ Khaled on Apple Music|website=iTunes|accessdate=10 December 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Medasin Dance2\"/>\n|-\n| Mike Cruz Dance Remix\n| <ref name=\"mcd\">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/wild-thoughts-feat-rihanna-bryson-tiller-mike-cruz/1259403457|title=Wild Thoughts (feat. Rihanna & Bryson Tiller) [Mike Cruz Dance Remix] \u2013 Single by DJ Khaled on Apple Music|website=iTunes|accessdate=10 December 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"mcd2\"/>\n|-\n| NOTD Dance Remix\n| <ref name=\"NOTD Dance\">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/wild-thoughts-feat-rihanna-bryson-tiller-notd-dance/1259401680|title=Wild Thoughts (feat. Rihanna & Bryson Tiller) [NOTD Dance Remix] \u2013 Single by DJ Khaled on Apple Music|website=iTunes|accessdate=10 December 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"NOTD DanceII\"/>\n|-\n|}\n\n==Fines==\nIn 2018, [[Turkey]]\u2019s top media watchdog, the [[Radio and Television Supreme Council]] (RT\u00dcK), reviewed the English-language lyrics of the song, and issued fines after concluding that they were inappropriate. RT\u00dcK issued a 17,065 Turkish Lira fine to the Turkish music channels NR1 and [[Dream TV (Turkey)|Dream TV]].<ref>[http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/turkeys-media-watchdog-issues-fine-over-rihanna-lyrics-132975 Turkey\u2019s media watchdog issues fine over Rihanna lyrics]</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of Airplay 100 number ones of the 2010s]]\n*[[List of top 10 singles in 2017 (Australia)]]\n*[[List of Billboard Hot 100 top 10 singles in 2017|List of ''Billboard'' Hot 100 top 10 singles of 2017 (U.S.)]]\n*[[List of number-one dance singles of 2017 (U.S.)]]\n*[[List of number-one R&B/hip-hop songs of 2017 (U.S.)|List of ''Billboard'' number-one R&B/hip-hop songs of 2017 (U.S.)]]\n*[[List of Billboard Rhythmic number-one songs of the 2010s#2017|List of ''Billboard'' number-one Rhythmic songs of 2017 (U.S.)]]\n*[[List of UK Singles Chart number ones of the 2010s#2017|List of UK Singles Chart number ones of 2017]]\n*[[List of UK R&B Singles Chart number ones of 2017]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Youtube|fyaI4-5849w|\"Wild Thoughts\"}}\n* {{MetroLyrics song|DJ-Khaled|Wild-Thoughts}}\n\n{{DJ Khaled songs}}\n{{Rihanna songs}}\n{{Bryson Tiller}}\n\n[[Category:2017 singles]]\n[[Category:2017 songs]]\n[[Category:Bryson Tiller songs]]\n[[Category:DJ Khaled songs]]\n[[Category:Rihanna songs]]\n[[Category:Music videos directed by Colin Tilley]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Carlos Santana]]\n[[Category:Songs written by DJ Khaled]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Rihanna]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Wyclef Jean]]\n[[Category:Billboard Dance Club Songs number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Billboard Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs number-one singles]]\n[[Category:UK Singles Chart number-one singles]]\n[[Category:UK R&B Singles Chart number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Songs about sexuality]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Romania]]\n[[Category:Songs written by PartyNextDoor]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Jerry Duplessis]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Bryson Tiller]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2017 single by DJ Khaled}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Wild Thoughts\n| cover      = Wild Thoughts cover.png\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[DJ Khaled]] featuring [[Rihanna]] and [[Bryson Tiller]]\n| album      = [[Grateful (DJ Khaled album)|Grateful]]\n| released   = June 16, 2017\n| format     = {{hlist|[[CD single|CD]]|[[Music download|digital download]]}}\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Latin pop]]|[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]}}\n| length     = {{duration|m=3|s=24}}\n| label      = {{hlist|[[We the Best Music Group|We the Best]]|[[Epic Records|Epic]]}}\n| writer     = {{hlist|[[PartyNextDoor|Jahron Braithwaite]]|[[DJ Khaled|Khaled Khaled]]|[[Rihanna|Robyn Fenty]]|[[Bryson Tiller]]|[[Jerry Duplessis]]|[[Wyclef Jean]]|David McRae|Marvin Moore-Hough|[[Carlos Santana]]}}\n| producer   = {{hlist|DJ Khaled|DJ Nasty|PartyNextDoor|Carlos Santana}}\n| chronology = [[DJ Khaled]]\n| prev_title = [[I'm the One (DJ Khaled song)|I'm the One]]\n| prev_year  = 2017\n| next_title = [[Top Off]]\n| next_year  = 2018\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Rihanna]]\n | type       = singles\n | prev_title = [[Selfish (Future song)|Selfish]]\n | prev_year  = 2017\n | title      = Wild Thoughts\n | year       = 2017\n | next_title = [[Loyalty (Kendrick Lamar song)|Loyalty]]\n | next_year  = 2017\n}}\n{{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Bryson Tiller]]\n | type       = singles\n | prev_title = [[Somethin Tells Me]]\n | prev_year  = 2017\n | title      = Wild Thoughts\n | year       = 2017\n | next_title = [[Run Me Dry]]\n | next_year  = 2017\n}}{{External music video|{{YouTube|fyaI4-5849w|\"Wild Thoughts\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''Wild Thoughts'''\" is a song by American musician [[DJ Khaled]] featuring Barbadian singer [[Rihanna]] and American singer [[Bryson Tiller]]. It was released on June 16, 2017, by [[We the Best Music Group|We the Best]] and [[Epic Records]] as the third single from Khaled's tenth studio album, ''[[Grateful (DJ Khaled album)|Grateful]]'' (2017).<ref name=\"ew\">{{cite web|url=http://ew.com/music/2017/06/15/dj-khaled-rihanna-collaboration-wild-thoughts/|title=DJ Khaled reveals details of 'humongous' Rihanna collab, 'Wild Thoughts'|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|first=Eric|last=Renner Brown|date=June 15, 2017|accessdate=June 15, 2017}}</ref> Canadian singer [[PartyNextDoor]] assisted the artists in writing the song, with production handled by Khaled. A mid-tempo pop song, \"Wild Thoughts\" consists of Latin percussion, [[acoustic guitar]] lines and riffs that interpolate the 1999 hit single \"[[Maria Maria]]\" by [[Santana (band)|Santana]]. Lyrically, the song praises a lover who inspires sexual thoughts.\n\nCommercially, the song reached number one in the United Kingdom, marking Khaled's second and Rihanna's ninth number one. The song also saw chart success in Australia and Canada, where it peaked at number two. The song peaked at number two on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], becoming Rihanna's 31st top-ten song, Khaled's third, and Tiller's first.\n\nThe [[music video]] for the song was directed by [[Colin Tilley]] and was shot in the [[Little Haiti]] neighborhood of [[Miami, Florida]]. The music video was nominated in three categories at the [[MTV Video Music Award]]s for [[MTV Video Music Award for Video of the Year|Video of the Year]], [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Collaboration|Best Collaboration]] and [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Art Direction|Best Art Direction]].\n\n==Background and composition==\nBryson Tiller and Khaled had first collaborated on the track \"Ima Be Alright\" for Khaled's ninth studio album ''[[Major Key (album)|Major Key]]'' (2016).<ref>{{cite web|title=DJ Khaled Details Major Key Tracklist Featuring Kanye, Jay Z, Drake, Future, Kendrick Lamar, More|url=http://pitchfork.com/news/66348-dj-khaled-details-new-album-major-key-featuring-kanye-jay-z-drake-future-kendrick-lamar-more/|work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|accessdate=June 15, 2017|date=July 23, 2016}}</ref> During ''Grateful''{{'}}s recording, Khaled invited Tiller to his house for dinner. During dinner, Khaled played the initial demo of \"Wild Thoughts\" to Tiller and asked him if he could do something with the song. Tiller returned home and recorded his verse and sent it to Khaled who used it on the final recording.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.harpersbazaar.com/culture/art-books-music/a10252969/bryson-tiller-interview/|title=Bryson Tiller on How His Collab with Rihanna and DJ Khaled Came to Life|date=3 July 2017|website=harpersbazaar.com}}</ref> While talking about collaborating with Rihanna for the first time in an interview with ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'', Khaled said; \"Seven, eight years I've been trying to do this. I always put the kites out there that I wanted to work with her. But at the same time, while I was putting the kites out there, I was always getting the right record ready. You've gotta start with the right energy to see if something comes back that\u2019s possible.\"<ref name=\"ew\" />\n\n\"Wild Thoughts\" is a mid-tempo [[Pop rock]] song with Latin percussion and \"slinky acoustic guitar lines.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://radio.com/2017/06/16/dj-khaled-wild-thoughts-rihanna-bryson-tiller/|title=DJ Khaled Drops 'Wild Thoughts' Video Featuring Rihanna & Bryson Tiller|website=radio.com |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170616142027/http://radio.com/2017/06/16/dj-khaled-wild-thoughts-rihanna-bryson-tiller/|archivedate=June 16, 2017|accessdate=October 13, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Cirisano|first=Tatiana|title=Product G&B Talk 'Maria Maria' and 'Wild Thoughts': Interview|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7849262/product-gb-maria-maria-wild-thoughts-sample-interview|accessdate=May 8, 2018|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=June 29, 2017}}</ref> The song heavily samples the guitar riff from Santana's 1999 \"Maria Maria\", which features [[The Product G&B]].<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=http://time.com/4820878/5-songs-you-need-to-listen-to-this-week-16/|title=5 Songs You Need to Listen to This Week|first=Raisa|last=Bruner|website=Time}}</ref> Written in the key of C minor, it has a [[tempo]] of 96-100 beats per minute in [[Duple and quadruple meter|simple quadruple ({{Time signature|4|4}}) time]]. The song follows a chord progression of Cm\u2013Fm\u2013Cm, and Rihanna's and Tiller's vocals spanning from C<sub>4</sub> to G<sub>5</sub>.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtd.asp?ppn=MN0175049|title=DJ Khaled Feat. Rihanna & Bryson Tiller \"Wild Thoughts\" Sheet Music in C Minor (transposable) \u2013 Download & Print|first=Khaled, Khaled|last=M|website=Musicnotes.com}}</ref> ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' editor Andrew Unterberger noted the \"Wild Thoughts\" featured the same groove and riff as \"Maria Maria\" and even featured Wyclef Jean's \"murmuring\" who supplied the original songs ad-libs.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7833809/santana-maria-maria-rob-thomas-smooth-dj-khaled-rihanna-wild-thoughts|title=It's Time for 'Maria Maria' to Replace 'Smooth' As the Santana Meme Song |work=Billboard |date=June 16, 2017|accessdate=June 16, 2017}}</ref> Vanessa Okoth-Obbo of ''Pitchfork'' described the track as relying heavily on a \"Latin rock aesthetic\", with lyrics that hear Rihanna and Tiller croon praise lovers who inspire wild thoughts. Okoth-Obbo described the lyrics as straddling the line between \"innuendos and carnal statements\", whilst also noting the singers\u2019 vocal performances as being restrained and controlled.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pitchfork.com/reviews/tracks/dj-khaled-wild-thoughts/|title=\"Wild Thoughts\" Review \u2013 Pitchfork|website=pitchfork.com}}</ref>\n\n==Release and reception==\n[[File:Carlos Santana 2.jpg|thumb|right|\"Wild Thoughts\" heavily samples \"[[Maria Maria]]\" performed by Santana. Guitarist Carlos Santana praised the use of the song]]\nOn June 9, 2017, Khaled released the album's track listing, which also included \"Wild Thoughts\".<ref name=\"xxl\">{{cite web|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2017/06/dj-khaled-grateful-album-tracklist/|title=DJ Khaled Reveals Star-Studded \u2018Grateful\u2019 Album Tracklist|work=[[XXL (magazine)|XXL]]|date=June 9, 2017|accessdate=June 16, 2017}}</ref> The song's artwork, which features Khaled's son Asahd, was revealed via Rihanna's [[Instagram]] account on June 15, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/7833688/dj-khaled-rihanna-bryson-tiller-wild-thoughts-grateful|title=DJ Khaled's 'Wild Thoughts' Collaboration With Rihanna and Bryson Tiller Will Drop Tomorrow|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=June 15, 2017|accessdate=June 16, 2017}}</ref> \"Wild Thoughts\" was released on June 16, 2017, as the album's third single.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hotnewhiphop.com/dj-khaled-rihanna-and-bryson-tillers-wild-thoughts-dropping-tomorrow-news.33810.html|title=DJ Khaled, Rihanna, & Bryson Tiller's \"Wild Thoughts\" Dropping Tomorrow|work=HotNewHipHop|date=June 15, 2017|accessdate=June 16, 2017}}</ref> ''Grateful'' was released on June 23, 2017.<ref name=\"xxl\" />\n\nPeter A. Berry from ''[[XXL (magazine)|XXL]]'' wrote; \"If all goes according to plan, it should go follow in the footsteps of \"[[I'm the One (DJ Khaled song)|I'm the One]]\" and reach platinum status in the very near future.\"<ref name=\"xxl2\" /> Janelle Okwode of ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'' said that the song \"is an instant contender for song of the summer\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vogue.com/article/rihanna-dj-khaled-wild-thoughts-video-fashion-fantasy|title=Of Course DJ Khaled and Rihanna\u2019s New Video is a Wild Fashion Fantasy|work=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]|date=June 16, 2017|accessdate=June 16, 2017}}</ref> Raisa Bruner from ''Time'' magazine listed the song on her list of five songs that should be heard. Bruner praised the song calling it an \"irresistible, Latin-inflected summer jam with some smooth verses courtesy of the addition of Bryson Tiller.\" Bruner continued to state that the song was truly Rihanna's  \"but we all know this is Rihanna's show.\"<ref name=\"auto\" /> In a second and more in-depth review Burner stated:\n\n{{cquote|\"Wild Thoughts\" kicks off with a bang and that instantly-recognizable Santana guitar melody, before segueing into Rihanna's low, compelling vocals and Tiller's verses. It feels like a spiritual successor to last year's hits \"Work\" and \"One Dance\" \u2014 but swapping those songs' dancehall vibes for Santana's guitar. Either way, it's an intoxicating bop guaranteed to heat things up.}}\n\n[[Uproxx]]'s Corbin Reiff wrote that Rihanna \"brings some serious heat\", while Tiller \"rolls through in the middle to reprise his verse, and brings some serious R&B vibes with along him\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uproxx.com/realtalk/dj-khaled-and-rihanna-wild-thoughts/|title=DJ Khaled And Rihanna Keep Things Smooth In Their Spanish-Flavored \u2018Wild Thoughts\u2019 Video|work=[[Uproxx]]|date=June 16, 2017|accessdate=June 16, 2017}}</ref>\nMatt Miller of ''[[Esquire (magazine)|Esquire]]'' praised Rihanna's saying that she \"completely commands the song, the power of her voice, her presence takes the entire thing over.\" Miller was less favourable about Tiller and the Santana sample calling their inclusion forgettable.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.esquire.com/entertainment/music/news/a55683/dj-khaled-rihanna-wild-thoughts-video/|title=It Was Nice of Rihanna to Let DJ Khaled Put His Name on This Song|work=[[Esquire (magazine)|Esquire]]|date=June 16, 2017|accessdate=June 16, 2017}}</ref>\n''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' editor Andrew Unterberger wrote that this is \"practically a cover with different lyrics\" of \"Maria Maria\", saying that it is \"not a perfect song, but it's a super-fun resurrection of the now 18-year-old single\".<ref name=\"auto1\" /> Elias Leight from ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' called it \"another warm-weather-friendly single\" by Khaled.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/see-dj-khaled-rihanna-in-sultry-wild-thoughts-video-w488291|title=See DJ Khaled, Rihanna, Bryson Tiller in Sultry 'Wild Thoughts' Video|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=June 16, 2017|accessdate=June 16, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Carlos Santana's response===\n[[Carlos Santana]] who originally wrote \"Maria Maria\", the song which is sampled on \"Wild Thoughts\", praised Khaled's, Rihanna's and Tiller's take on the song. Stating \"There is a reason that the infectious groove/theme that Wyclef and I created on 'Maria Maria' still resonates today. It speaks to the heart. DJ Khaled, Rihanna and Bryson take that vibe and bring it to a new dimension with 'Wild Thoughts,' but the groove and essence of the song is still intact.\" continuing to say, \"I am honored that DJ Khaled, Rihanna & Bryson felt the intense intentionality of 'Maria Maria' and have shared this summer vibe with the world.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hotnewhiphop.com/carlos-santana-approves-of-dj-khaled-rihanna-and-bryson-tillers-wild-thoughts-news.34054.html?|title=DJ Khaled, Rihanna & Bryson Tiller's \"Wild Thoughts\" Approved by Carlos Santana|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n[[The Product G&B]] who originally sang \"Maria Maria\" had a mixed response to \"Wild Thoughts\". They stated they were grateful and called the song a \"blessing\" noting that when they hear \"Wild Thoughts\" \"you hear 'Maria,' it\u2019s bringing awareness all around.\" However they believed that \"Wild Thoughts\" had stripped the original of its meaning and \"its association with West Side Story, where the musical's character \"Maria\" stood to represent both the grim reality of gang violence and poverty and the hope for a better life.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7849262/product-gb-maria-maria-wild-thoughts-sample-interview|title=Product G&B Talk Recording 'Maria Maria' & Being Sampled on 'Wild Thoughts' 17 Years Later: 'It's A Blessing'|website=billboard.com}}</ref>\n\n==Commercial performance==\nOn June 26, \"Wild Thoughts\" debuted at number four on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], with 89,000 digital copies sold and 36.3 million streams. The song marked Rihanna's 31st top-ten, Khaled's third and Tiller's first. The song's debut additionally marked the third-highest debut of Rihanna's 60 Hot 100 entries and made Rihanna the fourth woman to make at least 60 Hot 100 appearances, joining [[Nicki Minaj]] (78), [[Aretha Franklin]] (73) and [[Taylor Swift]] (70).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7842210/despacito-hot-100-number-one-7th-week-dj-khaled-rihanna-wild-thoughts|title='Despacito' Tops Hot 100 for 7th Week & DJ Khaled's 'Wild Thoughts,' Featuring Rihanna & Bryson Tiller, Debuts at No. 4|website=billboard.com}}</ref> In its second week the song rose to a new peak of three on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100, becoming the first song to debut in the top five and rise in its second week since Eminem's \"The Monster\", also featuring Rihanna (2013).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7850288/luis-fonsi-daddy-yankee-justin-bieber-despacito-hot-100-imagine-dragons-top-10|title=Luis Fonsi & Daddy Yankee Rule Hot 100, Imagine Dragons Hit Top 10|website=billboard.com}}</ref> After slipping to number four on the Hot 100, \"Wild Thoughts\" rebounded to peak in the runner-up slot and remained there for seven consecutive weeks, but was blocked off the top spot only by [[Luis Fonsi]], [[Daddy Yankee]] and [[Justin Bieber]]'s \"[[Despacito]]\". It also earned Rihanna her record-extending 29th Radio Songs top 10, continuing her lead over [[Mariah Carey]] (23). \"Wild Thoughts\" additionally peaked at number one on the [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs]] chart, becoming Rihanna's seventh number one, Khaled's third and Tiller's first.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7866232/despacito-hot-100-ten-weeks-ed-sheeran-top-5-record|title='Despacito' Leads Hot 100 for 10th Week, Ed Sheeran Ties Record & Shawn Mendes Hits Top 10|website=billboard.com}}</ref>\n\n\"Wild Thoughts\" became Khaled's and Tiller's first number-one song on the [[Dance Club Songs]], and Rihanna's 31st.<ref name=\"Wild Thoughts Dance Club\">{{cite web|last=Murray|first=Gordon|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7933932/dj-khaled-dance-club-songs-wild-thoughts|title=DJ Khaled Crowns Dance Club Songs for First Time With 'Wild Thoughts'|work=Billboard|date=August 18, 2017|accessdate=August 18, 2017}}</ref> It is Rihanna's fourth number-one on the chart in 2017, following \"[[Love on the Brain]]\", \"[[Sex with Me]]\" and \"[[Pose (Rihanna song)|Pose]]\", the most among all acts; she is one of only four acts to have achieved four number-ones in a calendar year, one of two to do so twice, and the only one to have done so five times.<ref name=\"Wild Thoughts Dance Club\"/> \"Wild Thoughts\" is also only one of four out of her 31 chart-toppers whereby Rihanna is not the lead artist.<ref name=\"Wild Thoughts Dance Club\"/>\n\nOn July 21, \"Wild Thoughts\" reached number one on the [[UK Singles Chart]].<ref name=\"UK\" /> It is Khaled's second number one in the UK following \"[[I'm the One (DJ Khaled song)|I'm the One]]\", Rihanna's ninth, and the first chart-topper for Tiller.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2017/07/21/dj-khaled-rihanna-bryson-tiller-hit-no-1-in-the-u-k-with-wild-thoughts/|title=DJ Khaled, Rihanna & Bryson Tiller Hit No. 1 In The U.K. With 'Wild Thoughts'|work=[[Forbes]]|last=McIntyre|first=Hugh|date=July 21, 2017|accessdate=July 22, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nThe [[music video]] for \"Wild Thoughts\", directed by [[Colin Tilley]], was shot in the [[Little Haiti]] neighborhood of Miami, Florida, in June 2017.<ref name=\"rapup\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2017/06/06/dj-khaled-rihanna-bryson-tiller-music-video-shoot/?image=1|title=DJ Khaled, Rihanna, & Bryson Tiller Shoot Video in Miami|work=[[Rap-Up]]|date=June 6, 2017|accessdate=June 15, 2017}}</ref> The first images from the shoot were released online on June 6, 2017.<ref name=\"rapup\" /> The video premiered via Khaled's [[Vevo]] channel on June 16, 2017.<ref name=\"ew\" /><ref name=\"xxl2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/video/2017/06/dj-khaled-rihanna-bryson-tiller-wild-thoughts-video/|title=DJ Khaled, Rihanna and Bryson Tiller Head to Little Haiti in \"Wild Thoughts\" Video|work=XXL|date=June 16, 2017|accessdate=June 16, 2017}}</ref>\nKatie Skinner from ''Billboard Magazine'' gave an in-depth review of Rihanna's fashion throughout the music video. Skinner stated that the video had an \"upbeat summer nightlife vibe in a tropical Miami setting\" which \"Rihanna and Khaled carry out that concept by dressing in bright-hued outfits, serving up some serious polychromatic summer looks straight off the runway.\"\nDuring a breakdown of the video Skinner stated that Rihanna's first look saw her wearing a \"psychedelic Balenciaga high-waisted floral-print leggings with matching \"Knife\" boots, a bright-pink vintage Betsey Johnson crop top and a pair of oversize crescent-shape Lynn Ban earrings.\" This was accompanied by a floral head scarf, green vintage Versace belt and a pair of pink Karen Walker sunglasses. In the following scene Rihanna wore a \"short turquoise off-the-shoulder silk chiffon dress by Alberta Ferretti\" along with a pair of gladiator sandals designed by Rihanna and Manolo Blahnik. During the last few seconds of the video, Rihanna stands beside Khaled and Tiller, wearing a bright nylon off-the-shoulder top and cargo pants designed by Matthew Adams Dolan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/lifestyle/7833840/rihanna-fashion-dj-khaled-wild-thoughts-video|title=Here Is Every Tropical Outfit Rihanna Wore in DJ Khaled's 'Wild Thoughts' Video|publisher=Billboard}}</ref>\n\n==Remixes==\nOn July 10, 2017, American rappers [[A Boogie wit da Hoodie]] and [[Fabolous]] released their remix of the song titled \"Wild Thots\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/rap-music/new-music/2017/07/a-boogie-wit-da-hoodie-fabolous-wild-thots/|title=A Boogie Wit Da Hoodie and Fabolous Rap About \"Wild Thots\" on New Single|work=XXL|date=July 10, 2017|accessdate=July 11, 2017}}</ref> Canadian singer and rapper [[Tory Lanez]] also released his remix of the track featuring American singer [[Trey Songz]] on July 21, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/tory-lanez-wild-thoughts-swave-session-feat-trey-songz-new-song.1975092.html|title=Tory Lanez - Wild Thoughts (Swave Session) Feat. Trey Songz|work=HotNewHipHop|date=July 21, 2017|accessdate=October 14, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" border=\"1\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Organization\n! Award\n! Result\n! R\n|-\n| rowspan=\"13\" | 2017\n| rowspan=\"4\" | [[2017 MTV Video Music Awards|MTV Video Music Awards]]\n| [[MTV Video Music Award for Video of the Year|Video of the Year]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n| rowspan=\"4\" | <ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/mtv-vmas-nominations-2017-list-full-1023884 |title=VMAs: Kendrick Lamar Tops Nominations as MTV Continues to Eliminate Gendered Categories |date=July 25, 2017 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |access-date=October 14, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Collaboration|Best Collaboration]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Art Direction|Best Art Direction]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| [[MTV Video Music Award for Song of Summer|Song of Summer]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[2017 BET Hip Hop Awards|BET Hip Hop Awards]]\n| Best Hip Hop Video\n| {{Nominated}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" | <ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.rap-up.com/2017/09/14/bet-hip-hop-awards-2017-nominees/|title=Kendrick Lamar, DJ Khaled, & Cardi B Lead BET Hip-Hop Awards 2017 Nominees|date=September 14, 2017|work=Rap-Up|accessdate=October 14, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best Collabo, Duo or Group\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| Single of the Year\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" | [[2017 Soul Train Music Awards|Soul Train Music Awards]]\n| [[Soul Train Music Award for Best Video of the Year|Best Video of the Year]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n| rowspan=\"5\" | <ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8005601/soul-train-awards-2017-nominees-solange-bruno-mars-bet | title=Solange, Bruno Mars Lead 2017 Soul Train Awards Nominations | work=Billboard | date=October 17, 2017 | accessdate=October 18, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Soul Train Music Award for Best Song of the Year|Best Song of the Year]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| [[Soul Train Music Award for Best Collaboration|Best Collaboration]]\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| [[Soul Train Music Award for Best Dance Performance|Best Dance Performance]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| [[Soul Train Music Award for Rhythm & Bars Award|Rhythm & Bars Award]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| [[2017 MTV Europe Music Awards|MTV Europe Music Awards]]\n| [[MTV Europe Music Award for Best Song|Best Song]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n| <ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/mtv-ema-nominations-2017-1045586/item/best-song-1045794|title=MTV EMAs: Taylor Swift Leads Nominations|date=October 4, 2017|work=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=October 14, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"7\" | 2018\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[2018 iHeartRadio Music Awards|iHeartRadio Music Awards]]\n| Song of the Year\n| {{Nominated}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" |\n|-\n| Best Collaboration\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| Hip-Hop Song of the Year\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| [[2018 Billboard Music Awards|''Billboard'' Music Awards]]\n| Top R&B Song\n| {{Nominated}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[BET Awards 2018|BET Awards]]\n| [[BET Award for Video of the Year|Video of the Year]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" |\n|-\n| [[BET Award for Viewer's Choice|Coca-Cola Viewer's Choice Award]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| [[BET Award for Best Collaboration|Best Collaboration]]\n| {{Won}}\n|}\n\n==Track listing==\n*'''Digital download'''\n#\"Wild Thoughts\" (featuring [[Rihanna]] and [[Bryson Tiller]]) \u2013 3:24\n\n*'''CD single'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/Thoughts-Khaled-Rihanna-Bryson-Tiller/dp/B0742W7BK9/|title=Wild Thoughts by DJ Khaled Feat. Rihanna and Bryson Tiller: Amazon.co.uk: Music|publisher=[[Amazon.com]]}}</ref>\n#\"Wild Thoughts\" (featuring Rihanna and Bryson Tiller) \u2013 3:24\n#\"Wild Thoughts\" (Medasin Dance Remix) (featuring Rihanna and Bryson Tiller) \u2013 4:35\n\n*'''Streaming \u2013 Bee's Knees Dance Remix '''<ref name=\"bkd2\">{{cite web|url=https://open.spotify.com/album/5JbSGf93cwzNRml2Gh0eA8|title=Wild Thoughts (Bee's Knees Dance Remix) by DJ Khaled on Spotify|publisher=[[Spotify]]}}</ref><ref name=\"bkd\"/>\n#\"Wild Thoughts\" (Bee's Knees Dance Remix) (featuring Rihanna and Bryson Tiller) \u2013 3:51\n\n*'''Streaming \u2013 Dave Aud\u00e9 Dance Remix'''<ref name=\"dad2\">{{cite web|url=https://open.spotify.com/album/2o1gol6Lhvb5ULwkwtZNCU|title=Wild Thoughts (Dave Aud\u00e9 Dance Remix) by DJ Khaled on Spotify|publisher=Spotify}}</ref><ref name=\"dad\"/>\n#\"Wild Thoughts\" ([[Dave Aud\u00e9]] Dance Remix) (featuring Rihanna and Bryson Tiller) \u2013 4:43\n\n*'''Streaming \u2013 Medasin Dance Remix'''<ref name=\"Medasin Dance2\">{{cite web|url=https://open.spotify.com/album/4guOdLBYRWg6av5iYzJdfm|title=Wild Thoughts (Medasin Dance Remix) by DJ Khaled on Spotify|publisher=Spotify}}</ref><ref name=\"Medasin Dance\"/>\n#\"Wild Thoughts\" (Medasin Dance Remix) (featuring Rihanna and Bryson Tiller) \u2013 4:35\n\n*'''Streaming \u2013 Mike Cruz Dance Remix''